"```json\n{\n\"title\": \"Medium - Word Frequency Counter\", \n\"description\": \"Write a function `word_frequency` that takes a string of text as input and returns a dictionary containing the frequency of each word in the text. Ignore capitalization and punctuation.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef word_frequency(text: str) -> dict:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `text` (str): A string of text.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns a dictionary where the keys are the unique words in the text and the values are their respective frequencies.\",\n\"code\": \"import re\\ndef word_frequency(text: str) -> dict:\\n    text = text.lower()\\n    words = re.findall(r'[a-z]+', text)\\n    frequency = {}\\n    for word in words:\\n        if word in frequency:\\n            frequency[word] += 1\\n        else:\\n            frequency[word] = 1\\n    return frequency\",\n\"tests\": [\n\"'assert word_frequency('This is a test. This is only a test.') == {'this': 2, 'is': 2, 'a': 2, 'test': 2, 'only': 1}'\",\n\"'assert word_frequency('The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.') == {'the': 2, 'quick': 1, 'brown': 1, 'fox': 1, 'jumps': 1, 'over': 1, 'lazy': 1, 'dog': 1}'\"\n]\n}```"